Recommended environment: Ubuntu 14.04

1. Install Docker, autoconf, git

2. Run `autoconf`

3. (optional) Copy your Rodan source code here as folder `Rodan`.

4a. For server run:
./configure MODE=server DB_PASSWORD="!@#%" DOMAIN_NAME="rodan.simssa.ca" WORKERS_SUBNET="192.168.125.0/24" CLIENT_MAX_BODY_SIZE=200M RODAN_DATA_DIR=/mnt/rodan_data

4b. For worker, run:
./configure MODE=worker DB_PASSWORD="!@#%" DB_HOST="192.168.125.2" CELERY_BROKER_URL="amqp://rodanuser:DDMALrodan@192.168.125.2:5672/DDMAL" SERVER_IP="192.168.125.2"

(If you skipped step 3, you need to provide `GIT_CLONE_URL="https://github.com/DDMAL/Rodan.git" BRANCH=develop` in step 4.)

5. Copy Kakadu source code in this folder (e.g. v7_7-01273N.zip)

6. Run `sh deploy.sh`


